Stefan Schnabel https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stefan_Schnabel 0 Stefan Artur Schnabel (February 2, 1912 – March 11,1999) was a German-born American actor who worked in theatre, radio, films and television. After moving to the United States in 1937 he became one of the original members of Orson Welles's Mercury Theatre repertory company. He portrayed Dr. Stephen Jackson on the CBS daytime TV series, The Guiding Light, for 17 years.
